===Etymology===
Probably an affectionate alteration of {{m|en|mama}} or reduplication of {{m|maw||mother}}.

The word Ma Maw  is termed as a slang word, derived from Glasweegian Strathclyde Gaelic Scots.  Ma is used when addressing ones own Mother, Maw is used when addressing others of ones own or others mothers ( aye yer maw, Glaswegian humour inferring disbelief with a hint of ridicule) 
Ma is also used to mean what is with you, what is beside you ( inferring ownership) when using both together,  Ma Maw translates to My Mother.

